race.comment: VASILIAS (3) was better here last start, giving a strong sight before being reeled in late and finishing fourth. He still has more to offer and is a leading player. LYRA STAR (2) finds the maiden win elusive but has been contesting solid races and holding her own. With the claim and a soft draw, she maps for the gun run and can give this a genuine shake. GAME OVER (1) looked ready to strike fresh but didn't quite finish off, and his second-up run was below expectations. Third-up now, he can bounce back sharply. GRINZINGER GOLD (6) hasn't threatened in two runs back, but the form around her reads well. Worth keeping safe.
